c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Canva and Framer share a solid foundation of core features including Templates, Drag And Drop, Brand Kit, Ai Generation. Where Canva pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Stock Assets, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Canva holds an overall score of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 10/10, while Framer scores 8/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Canva and Framer offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Canva's free tier and Framer's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
